NAME
    applfind - tests if a GEM application is loaded in memory

SYNOPSIS
    applfind <GEMAPP>

    <GEMAPP> name of GEM application targetted. Extension and
    		 path can be omited.
    
DESCRIPTION
    applfind command can be used to know is an GEM application is
    loaded in memory and ready to receive a message. Command returns
    AES process identificator or -1 if application is not
    loaded in memory.

SEE ALSO
    applwrit, vastart, avserver, open.


